FEAT (git feat): A new feature
FIX (git fx): A bug fix
DOCS (git doc): Documentation only changes
STYLE (git style): Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
REFACTOR (git refactor): A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
PERF (git perf): A code change that improves performance
TEST (git tst): Adding tests or correcting existing tests
BUILD (git build): Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (flutter, dart, riverpod, etc..)
CI (git ci): Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
LOCALIZE (git localize): Translations update
REVERT (git rvrt): Reverts a previous commit
RELEASE (git rlz): New release